    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The current military posture and activity patterns suggest an increased focus on the Middle East, with the USS Tripoli and the 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit transiting the Malacca Strait en route to the region. The USS Gerald R. Ford is in port at Souda Bay for repairs, indicating a temporary reduction in carrier strike group capabilities in the area. Aircraft activity is characterized by a mix of transport, training, ISR, and patrol operations, with a notable presence of C-17, C560, and PC-21 aircraft. The overall assessment is that the US military is maintaining a strong presence in the region, with a focus on supporting operations in the Middle East and ensuring the security of key waterways. The situation is dynamic, with ongoing operations against Iranian targets and a heightened state of alertness among regional forces.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
